Train Model
member.remarks: The train request must include a source parameter that is either an externally accessible Azure Storage blob container Uri (preferably a Shared Access Signature Uri) or valid path to a data folder in a locally mounted drive. When local paths are specified, they must follow the Linux/Unix path format and be an absolute path rooted to the input mount configuration setting value e.g., if '{Mounts:Input}' configuration setting value is '/input' then a valid source path would be '/input/contosodataset'. All data to be trained are expected to be under the source. Models are trained using documents that are of the following content type - 'application/pdf', 'image/jpeg' and 'image/png'." Other content is ignored when training a model.
member.param: Request object for training.
